Definition: the condition of a host bacterium that has incorporated a phage into its own genetic material
Example: when a phage infects a bacterium it can either destroy its host or be incorporated in the host genome in a state of lysogeny
Synonyms: adj, pert, lysogenic, lysogenicity, condition, the, of, a, host, bacterium, that, has, incorporated, phage, into, its, own, genetic, material, when, infects, it, can, either, destroy, or, be, in, genome, state
Category: noun.state
